It was a night of rhythm, glitz, and glam when Trace Live hosted Ghanaian musician, King Promise at Terra Kulture, Victoria Island, Lagos. The event started with comic relief by comedian Pencil, who took on the stage for about 30-minutes making sure the atmosphere was friendly with rib-cracking jokes and set for King Promise’s performance. Pencil went on to crack jokes until it was time for the man of the night to perform. King Promise, who was gaily dressed, got on the stage to thrill the audience with support from Alternate Sound’s four-man band. King Promise delivered a sterling performance, churning out popular hits after hits during the show which lasted  two hours.   Sir Adegoke Ogunwusi, Dele Gold, others embark on US, Canada…     How I deal with heartbreak, by Grace Agbo     Obi Cubana grateful to God at 47   One of the highlights of the live show was when Promise was joined by Mr Eazi to perform their collaboration. King  and Mr Eazi performed their collaborative effort ‘Odo’, as Eazi serenaded his girlfriend, Temi Otedola with the 2018 classic. He went on to perform other songs including Slow Down, Tokyo, Abena, Fine Wine, CCTV, and many more. The singer also paid a tribute to his Ghanaian countrymen, R2Bees by performing the hit song, ‘Kiss your hand.’ Some of the celebs spotted at the event include Bankuli, Mr Eazi, Temi Otedola, Tolani, Bizzle, Shody, and Tobi Bakare.